title: For Sale/Trade:  Sig P320 Subcompact 9mm x-change kit. Used twice, about 100 rounds.
location: Casselberry (just outside Orlando Area), Orlando, Florida
postcontent:
I know they're not releasing P320 Subcompact kits at the moment (hard enough to get 9mm compact), but I've decided I want to keep my FCU (trigger, serial, internals...) but sell the rest as an x-change kit. The difference is that kits only come with one magazine (nice magazines btw), but I have two 12 round 9mm mags for mine. It has the night sights (Siglites) and the "grip module" (frame) is Magpul FDE duracoated, it's a little darker in the picture than reality. It's the size small grip it comes with. Comes with the upper (slide and night sights, barrel, dual recoil spring guide rod,) as well as the "grip module" and and the 2 12 round magazines. This thing is great for concealed carry, similar to a Glock 26 or 27. Concealability, plus capacity, plus not going lower than 3.5 inches with the barrel. It's essentially a whole two tone FDE P320 subcompact minus the FCU (I might get another kit later, now I have bigger worries). I'm asking $275 for it all (or $315 with the compact 15 round mag and x-grip). They sell from Sig for 399 at the moment. Yes, with 20% discount you can swing $320 (IF they have it). You only get one mag though and they don't make the kits for Subcompact. It may not look as tacticool as a Compact, but it works much better for carry in my experience and there's only a .3 inch barrel length difference. So you're not buying a 3 inch Shield, it's well rounded in all ways. Unfortunately I have to get rid of one pistol right now and since I can get a kit later, I thought doing this would be best. It's been maintained (with it's siblings) religiously using NRA mil-comm grease, lubricant oil, and a green "safe" degreaser (which works, even the bore after a session). Sig recommends it and I can see why, everything functions so much better and smoother. I can give a sample small bottle I have of the grease (you use it the most)  also. Make me an offer if you wish (please don't play high/low games or lowball, just give me a straight number. No offer/counteroffer for 5 or 10 minutes. Not to say I won't hear an offer and then counteroffer if it's fair and I feel it should be bit more. Just not over and over. My number is REDACTED. I also have some ads for Glock 17 stock parts to check out if you're interested. FL ID also.

YOU MUST have a P320 of any size or at least a P320 FCU trigger unit alone for this kit to work. Without it, it has no trigger system.

postcontent:
Up for sale is my SW 5906 9MM.  I bought this pistol in 2012 and have probably put around 1000 rounds through it.  It has always functioned great and has never had any kind of malfunction or jam with any of the various types of ammo I have put through it.  It is in great shape with only very minor wear and tear you would see for a pistol this age.  It is equipped with a Hogue grip and of course the standard Novak sites.  

I am selling this pistol because I want to buy something different.  I am also selling this pistol because, honestly I dont think it shoots as straight as it should.  Im pretty sure its not me but I suppose it could be.  I tried a new recoil spring but it still does not shoot as straight as I would like.  I dont think the sights are off but I suppose that is possible.  Personally, I think it needs a new barrel but it could just as easily be something else or something very minor or just that I dont shoot it very well.  

As I said, it is in great shape and has always functioned flawlessly and is a really nice looking pistol.  I will include 2 15 round SW factory mags as well as 2 16 round Mecgar mags.  All of the mags work perfect.  I used the plastic box for something else so that is not included.  I will give the pistols and mags to the buyer in a cardboard box.  

I looked around and it looked like most of these are going for about $400 without extra mags.  Since this one might have a minor issue, I will let it go for $375 with the extra mags.  I am also open to offers so feel free to make an offer also!  

As per state law, ANY BUYER MUST HAVE A VALID PERMIT TO PURCHASE OR PERMIT TO CARRY.  I will be asking to see a valid permit and matching drivers license.
